# image-processing / G'MIC

G'MIC (GREYC's Magic for Image Computing) is an open-source image-processing framework exposing 4000+ filters through its own scriptable language. A chained pipeline string transforms input images and emits output files headlessly and deterministically. The recipe (`.gmic` pipeline) is the version-controllable artifact; the rendered raster **image** is the deliverable. This wrapper drives the `gmic` CLI — the most reliable headless driver (the Python binding's wheels lag behind current Python).

controls do
  image-processing.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  image-processing.pipeline: { label: "Pipeline", type: "textarea", file: "src/recipe.gmic" }
  image-processing.seed: { label: "Seed (srand)", type: "text" }
